  "prompt": "How do you know if a guy is obsessed with you?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone is obsessed with you can be complex and sensitive. Obsession is often characterized by intense and often irrational feelings or behaviors that go beyond normal interest or affection. Here are some signs that might indicate a guy is obsessed with you:\n\n1. **Excessive Communication**: He might text, call, or message you constantly, often expecting immediate responses and becoming agitated or upset if you don\u2019t reply quickly.\n\n2. **Overly Possessive Behavior**: He may show signs of jealousy or possessiveness, such as questioning you about your whereabouts, who you\u2019re with, or what you\u2019re doing. This can extend to trying to control who you spend time with or isolating you from friends and family.\n\n3. **Constant Monitoring**: He might try to keep tabs on your social media activities, track your location, or show up uninvited to places you frequent.\n\n4. **Intense Focus on You**: He talks about you incessantly, to the point where it seems like he has no other interests or focuses in life. His world seems to revolve around you.\n\n5. **Unwanted Gifts or Gestures**: He might give you excessive gifts or make grand gestures in an attempt to win your affection or attention, even if you\u2019ve made it clear you\u2019re not interested.\n\n6. **Ignoring Boundaries**: He disregards your personal boundaries and continues to pursue you despite clear signals that you\u2019re not interested or are uncomfortable with his actions.\n\n7. **Emotional Manipulation**: He may use guilt, pity, or other emotional tactics to keep you engaged with him, such as saying he can\u2019t live without you or that you\u2019re the only one who understands him.\n\n8. **Unpredictable or Erratic Behavior**: He might exhibit mood swings or erratic behaviors, such as being overly affectionate one moment and angry or sullen the next.\n\n9. **Inability to Accept Rejection**: If you\u2019ve rejected him or ended the relationship, he refuses to accept it and continues to pursue you or tries to convince you to change your mind.\n\n10. **Stalking or Harassment**: In extreme cases, he might follow you, show up at your home or workplace uninvited, or engage in other forms of harassment.\n\nIf you notice these signs, it's important to take them seriously. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n- **Set Clear Boundaries**: Communicate your boundaries clearly and firmly. Let him know what behaviors are unacceptable.\n- **Seek Support**: Talk to friends, family, or a counselor about your situation. They can offer support and advice.\n- **Document Incidents**: Keep a record of any concerning behaviors or incidents, as this can be helpful if you need to seek legal protection.\n- **Consider Legal Action**: If the behavior escalates to stalking or harassment, consider seeking a restraining order or other legal protections.\n\nRemember, your safety and well-being are paramount. If you feel threatened or unsafe, don\u2019t hesitate to reach out to local authorities or a support service.",
